==English==

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ʌk|-ʌk]]

===Noun===
'''chuck''' (''plural'' '''chucks''')

#[[Meat]] from the [[shoulder]] of a [[cow]] or other animal.
#The round part of a [[drill]] that holds the [[bit]]; in general a [[mechanical]] [[device]] to hold something [[rigid]]ly in place.
#(''slang'') An act of [[vomit]]ing.
#:''He went outside for a chuck.''
#A gentle touch.
#:''She gave him an affectionate chuck under the chin.''
#(''slang'') Friend or close [[acquaintance]]
#:''Are you alright chuck ?''

===Proper noun===
''See'' '''[[Chuck]]'''

===Transitive verb===
'''chuck''' ('''chucks''', '''chucking''', '''chucked''')

#(''Australia, UK, US, informal'') To [[throw]], esp. in a careless or inaccurate manner.
#:''Chuck that magazine to me, would you?''
#(''informal'') To [[discard]], to [[throw away]].
#:''This food's gone off - you'd better chuck it.''
#(''slang'') To [[consume]] wood in a rapid manner.
#:''That woodchuck chucked that wood like a rabid woodchuck!''

===Intransitive verb===
'''chuck''' ('''chucks''', '''chucking''', '''chucked''')

#(''slang'') To [[vomit]].
#{{cricket}} To [[throw]] the ball rather than [[bowl]] it.

